## 3. Technical Architecture

### 3-Tier Storage âœ… Verified

| Tier | Implementation | File | Purpose |
|------|---------------|------|---------|
| Tier 1 | JSON file (hot cache) | [tier1.ts](file:///c:/Users/abhis/Desktop/fullstackoverweekend/MemoryLayer/src/storage/tier1.ts) | Active session, recent decisions, immediate context |
| Tier 2 | SQLite (persistent) | [tier2.ts](file:///c:/Users/abhis/Desktop/fullstackoverweekend/MemoryLayer/src/storage/tier2.ts) | Files, symbols, decisions, dependencies, embeddings |
| Tier 3 | Vector search (in-memory) | Computed from Tier 2 embeddings | Semantic search via cosine similarity |

### AST Parser â€” âš ï¸ Partially Accurate

| Claimed | Actual |
|---------|--------|
| "Tree-sitter AST parsing" | âŒ Tree-sitter is **stubbed out** â€” `loadLanguage()` returns `null` |
| "AST Parser (understands code structure)" | âš ï¸ Uses **regex parsing**, not AST |
| Regex parsing for 6 languages | âœ… TS/JS, Python, Go, Rust, Java all have regex parsers |

> [!WARNING]
> The `NeuronLayer_Complete_Changes.md` document describes tree-sitter integration as a **future improvement**, not a current feature. However, `SIMPLE-EXPLANATION.md` and `WHAT-I-BUILT.md` mention "AST Parser" and "Tree-sitter for AST" as if they're current features. The README correctly says "regex parsing."
> 
> **Fix:** Update `SIMPLE-EXPLANATION.md` and `WHAT-I-BUILT.md` to say "regex-based parsing" instead of implying tree-sitter is active. The dependency `web-tree-sitter` is in `package.json` but isn't actively used.

### Build & Distribution âœ…

- **Single bundle:** `dist/index.js` (1.3MB) via esbuild
- **npm package:** `neuronlayer` v0.1.9
- **CLI binary:** `neuronlayer` command registered in package.json
- **Node.js 18+** required

